THIS IS A STORY ABOUT A MIDDLE AGED NURSE THAT BECOMES THE MAJOR FOCUS OF ONE MANS ATTENTION. SO BASICALLY HE PURSUES,AND PURSUES  HER UNTIL HE GETS WHAT HE WANTS. EVENTUALLY HE GETS HER INTO HIS LIFE, THEY MARRY, AND THEN ALL HELL BREAKS LOOSE; LITERALLY. NOT TO GIVE TOO MUCH AWAY ALL I'LL SAY IS SHE BETTER WATCH OUT FOR HER STEPSON.
I ordered this just because I wanted to see Josh Morrow in something besides The Young and the Restless. While it isn't a great film, it served it's purpose for me.
I got the movie in the amount of time I was told, only thing I was not happy with was, the disk was loose in the case, so the movie is all scratched, I have not tried to play it yet,
No sound track. Guess this woud be a great movie for the Deaf. But I figure Rachel Ward's beauty is worthy of at least one star.
